{"questionId":"25035008","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elsie, a librarian, wants to investigate the length of time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> minutes, that people spent in her library on a particular day.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elsie’s data for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn></math> people who visited the library on that particular day is shown in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a22ae009c52eae231f00243099926ab50be0a3cb.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elsie assumes her data to be representative of future visitors to the library.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability a visitor spends at least <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> minutes in the library.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>22</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>138</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1375</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>80</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct numerator, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct denominator.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25035008","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.1f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability a visitor spends at least 60 minutes in the library.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[